        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-15 08:44:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(4 comments)",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "f7f1dfb005cf4edbcfa5446c45710362dd4b40f4",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6868,
          "name": "Illia Halych",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "illia.halych@t-mobile.pl",
          "username": "elihalych"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-15 12:44:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> does it work with helm2 and helm3?\n\nSorry for the delay. So,\n\nPyhelm's official documentation says it supports Helm up to version 2.14: https://pypi.org/project/pyhelm/#package-versions\n\nI found this open issue for Pyhelm about the Helm 3 support that's still open since Sep 2019: https://github.com/flaper87/pyhelm/issues/84\n\nIf it's required that Helm 3 is supported with a given library, then the other most advertised tool is https://github.com/zbrookle/avionix . I will test this one",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "ab148637fd66eb422ae05db1d7bf0ba6617fcffd",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6868,
          "name": "Illia Halych",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "illia.halych@t-mobile.pl",
          "username": "elihalych"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-16 12:32:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> > Patch Set 3:\n> > \n> > does it work with helm2 and helm3?\n> \n> Sorry for the delay. So,\n> \n> Pyhelm's official documentation says it supports Helm up to version 2.14: https://pypi.org/project/pyhelm/#package-versions\n> \n> I found this open issue for Pyhelm about the Helm 3 support that's still open since Sep 2019: https://github.com/flaper87/pyhelm/issues/84\n> \n> If it's required that Helm 3 is supported with a given library, then the other most advertised tool is https://github.com/zbrookle/avionix . I will test this one\n\nTested Pyhelm with Helm3 and it fails. So only Helm 2 is operational with Pyhelm.\n\nAvionix however officially supports only Helm 3, not Helm 2.\nhttps://github.com/zbrookle/avionix/issues/53",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
